== Squad Composition ==
The standard Talsia squad is built around a specific philosophy: '''maximum projected shielding, combined with drain to neutralise enemy shield projectors, and concentrated firepower'''. Here is why each bot type matters:

=== The Core Formula ===
A typical Talsia squad consists of:
* '''3 Attack Bots''' — [[Crusader]] and/or [[Bulwark]], [[Reaper]]
* '''1 [[CySentinel]]''' — provides projected shielding for the entire squad; the stronger the [[CySentinel]], the more punishment the squad absorbs
* '''4 [[Seer|Seers]]''' — the most critical element; they determine fire rate, accuracy, energy savings, critical hit chance, and deflection

{{MessageBox
| header = Why 4 Seers?
| text   = Some Controllers use 5 Seers, and some use 3 with an extra attack bot. Testing has shown that 4 Seers reaches the same fire rate and deflection thresholds as 5, without the additional drain on energy. With 4 Seers, you can still hit maximum fire rate while keeping your attack bots fully energised for their weapons.
}}

=== Targeting Priority — Critical Setting ===
This is the most important configuration to get right when entering Talsia:
* '''[[Reaper]] / drain bots:''' Set '''Manual Targeting → Highest Shield Projector'''. The [[Reaper]]'s [[Syphonic Immobilizer|Immobilizer]] (and later the [[Rayden Device]]) will automatically target enemy shield projectors — this is essential for neutralising [[Ae7 Barrier Tank]]s, [[SR180 Receptor]] drain turrets, [[True Guard Shielding]], and Uplink Command towers.
* '''[[Crusader]] / [[Bulwark]]:''' Set to '''Highest Weapon Potential''' or manual targeting as needed.
* When hiring [[Basilisk]] (CyCorps Reaper merc): ensure squad targeting includes "Highest Shield Projector" so the Basilisk hits shielders automatically.

