==== Phase 2 Strategy ====
[[File:Cycorps_reaper.jpg|thumb|right|220px|[[Basilisk]] — the essential drain mercenary for Alpha Sector.]]

'''General Alpha rules:'''
* Avoid all random infantry and tank encounters in open patrol — tanks will kill you outright
* Save all KCharge for missions; skip Destroyers, Fire Bases, and Bunkers if low on KC
* Do Bunkers and Relay Stations when KC allows (3 Accolades and 15 MRP respectively — easy)
* '''Avoid TRAFs, Battle Cruisers, and Carrier SOS until Phase 4/5''' — they will kill your squad

'''Mission priority in Alpha:'''
# '''Destroy Cruiser''' — '''Never abort this mission''' (until 18k TRP). 100 TRP, the best single mission in the game. Hire [[Basilisk]] + [[Remus]] for safety.
# '''Reinforce Besieged Base''' — Best early Alpha mission. You get a base with increased deflections. Hire Basilisk. Hard if drain tanks have good uplinks.
# '''Mining Facility Raid''' — Usually easy; always get 5 tons and leave. Can be deadly if unlucky with tank composition.
# '''Blockade''' — Hardest Alpha mission. [[Crash Troopers]] can kill you in second turn — kill as many as possible on turn 1. Hire [[Typhoon]] for Crash Troopers. Use Magma Mines to lower BM of attacking squads.
# '''Chassis Recovery''' — Easiest Alpha mission; get 5 chassis and leave.
# '''Free Patrol''' — Do not take this mission; poor TRP/MRP ratio.

'''Target priority when fighting tanks:'''
# Drain [[Ae7 Barrier Tank]] / Shield Tanks first (their projected shields protect everything else)
# Kill/drain [[C6II Enertron]] / Inductor Tanks (they drain your squad)
# Kill Uplink Tanks (Command, Director, Syncron — boost accuracy and fire rate)
# Kill Heavy Siege Tanks first among damage dealers
# Kill remaining tanks

'''When hiring mercs:'''
* Only hire mercs in Alpha Sector
* '''[[Basilisk]]''' — essential for any mission with shield projectors (auto-drains them)
* '''[[Remus]]''' — valuable for 9% shield deflection and 11% drain deflection; great with Cruiser missions
* '''[[Typhoon]]''' — for Blockade missions with Crash Troopers
* [[Eclipse]] — extra 1,600 projected shielding for extra safety

