== TRAF Guide ==
[[File:Turret8.png|thumb|right|220px|[[SR180 Receptor]] — the deadliest drain turret in Talsia; cannot be targeted until walls are down.]]
[[File:Tank_manium2.png|thumb|right|220px|True Guard assembly — the final TRAF round.]]

A '''TRAF''' (Tactical Re-Arming Facility) is the hardest repeatable encounter in Talsia, rewarding '''75 TRP''' upon completion and a chance to receive the legendary '''[[Ravager]]''' super weapon.

TRAFs are discovered via '''Incoming Transmission''' orders (target the TRAF for destruction) or by stumbling across a '''TRAF Located''' event during patrol.

=== When to Attempt TRAFs ===
* '''Do not attempt TRAFs until Phase 4''' at minimum (Pneumatron + MFD Seers)
* Recommended minimums before your first TRAF:
  ** 10,000+ projected shielding on [[CySentinel]] (including mercs)
  ** 75%+ energy drain deflection on your squad
  ** [[Obliterator]] with 20%+ crit rate on [[Crusader]] (for breaking [[Reinforced Wall]] deflection)
  ** Hired [[Remus]] (9% shield deflection + 11% drain deflection) and [[Basilisk]] (drain assist)

=== TRAF Round-by-Round ===

'''Round 1 — Outer Defences:'''
[[File:Turret3.png|thumb|right|180px|PR600 Launcher — standard TRAF outer turret.]]
* Uplink Commands (×2, up to ×3 at high BM) — project 9,000 shield each; provide heavy armour/shield deflection
* Rhino turrets — deal ~5,000 damage (up to 15,000 with crits, though infrequent)
* FGSI Turrets — deal shield damage and drain; very active and crit-prone
* '''FGSI turrets stop operating when Uplink Commands are destroyed'''

'''Strategy:'''
# Turn 1: Drain both Uplink Commands with all drain bots
# Turn 2+: Kill the Uplink Commands once drained
# FGSI turrets become inactive once Commands are dead — mop up the rest
# Rhinos do manageable damage — kill in order of remaining threats

'''Round 2 — Wall Turrets:'''
[[File:Fedwall1.png|thumb|right|180px|Reinforced Wall — must be killed, not just drained.]]
* Reinforced Wall (×1) — provides drain deflection to all units behind it; [[SR180 Receptor]]s and Uplink Commands '''cannot be drained until the wall is killed'''
* SR180 Receptor (×1–2) — heavy drain turrets that crit frequently; the most dangerous drain sources in the game
* Uplink Commands (×2–3)
* Rhino turrets

'''Critical:''' The [[Reinforced Wall]] must be '''killed''' (not just drained) before the SR180 Receptors or Uplink Commands can be drained. Without a high-crit [[Obliterator]] or [[Ravager]] on [[Crusader]], breaking its deflection is very difficult.

'''Strategy:'''
# Turn 1: ALL attack the Reinforced Wall until it is dead
# Once the wall is down: drain Uplink Commands and SR180 Receptors
# Kill SR180s as a priority (they drain your squad heavily when active)
# Mop up remaining turrets

'''Round 3 — Inner Wall:'''
* Same as Round 2 but with additional tanks
* The tanks add moderate damage — not dramatically harder than Round 2
* Use the same approach: wall first, then drain, then kill SR180s

'''Round 4 — True Guard (Final Round):'''
[[File:Superinfantry.png|thumb|right|180px|True Guard infantry — high-damage, high-crit-rate elite units.]]
[[File:Tank_manium.png|thumb|right|180px|[[Storm Bringer]] — True Guard tank variant.]]

* '''[[True Guard]]''' infantry — deal ~6,000 damage with crits (very frequent crit rate)
* '''Manium Firespray''' — True Guard support unit; deals ~6,000 damage with crits
* '''[[Storm Bringer]]''' tanks — deal ~10,500 damage with crits (less frequent)
* '''Cortex Tanks''' — True Guard [[Seer|Seer]] equivalent; provide deflection, fire rate, and energy bonuses
* '''SR180 Receptors''' — still present; drain threat continues
* '''True Guard Shielding''' (×2, up to ×3 at 10M+ BM) — project massive shields; must be drained (not killed) to neutralise the True Guard formation

'''Warning:''' Do not stop or recover before Round 4. If you stop/recover after Round 3, you trigger another Round 3 equivalent instead of Round 4 — wasting KC and progress.

'''Strategy:'''
# Assign [[Reaper]] (with [[Rayden Device]]) to True Guard Shielding 1
# Assign hired [[Basilisk]] to True Guard Shielding 2 (and 3 if present)
# At 10M+ BM with 3 Shieldings: hire a second [[Basilisk]] for the third shielding
# A crit from [[Rayden Device]] first turn can drain all shields simultaneously
# Once shields are drained: kill SR180 Receptors first, then True Guard and Storm Tanks

=== TRAF Rewards ===
* '''75 Talsian Rank Points'''
* '''Rare: [[Ravager]]''' super weapon
  ** 3,000 shield damage / 1,750 armour damage / 500 drain
  ** Weight: 500 kg — requires 676+ Weapon Tech on [[Crusader]] and high payload
  ** ''One of the best weapons in the game — if you get it, restructure [[Crusader]] around it''

