== Dangerous Enemies ==
[[File:Tank_syphon.png|thumb|right|180px|[[C6II Enertron]] — the Inductor Tank; its [[Induction Device]] drains entire squads.]]

Talsia has many encounter types, but most can be skipped to conserve KC. The following are the threats that require the most careful handling.

=== Priority Drain Targets ===
Always drain these before they fire:
* '''[[Ae7 Barrier Tank]] / Shield Tank''' — projects 19,200+ shield for the entire formation; drain first or nothing else dies
* '''[[C6II Enertron]] / Inductor Tank''' — fires [[Induction Device]]; drains your entire squad's energy; must be drained/killed immediately
* '''[[Uplink Command]] tower''' — projects 9,000 shield; provides armour/shield deflection to all behind it
* '''[[Reinforced Wall]]''' — provides drain deflection to all units; kill it first
* '''True Guard Shielding''' — projects massive shields for True Guard formation; drain to neutralise

=== Extremely Dangerous Encounters (Avoid Early) ===
* '''[[True Guard]] (in open patrol)''' — Elite Federate faction; very high crit rate; 6,000+ damage per crit. Only engage when Phase 4+ with full merc support. In Carrier SOS events, easier than TRAF variants.
* '''[[Crash Troopers]]''' — Elite jetpack infantry. Can kill a bot on turn 2. Kill as many as possible on turn 1. Hire [[Typhoon]] merc to help.
* '''[[SR180 Receptor]] drain turrets''' — Cannot be targeted until Uplink Commands and Reinforced Walls are down. Deal enormous drain damage. Avoid their section until walls are cleared.
* '''[[Storm APC]]''' — transports [[Storm Troopers]] in Blockade missions; manage these carefully
* '''[[Battle Cruiser]]''' — Only engage in Phase 4+. Long-range bombardment phase + heavy engagement. 75 TRP reward.

=== Events to Never Skip ===
These are easy free resources during patrol:
* '''[[Bunkers]]''' — 3 Accolades each; easy fights or avoidable entirely
* '''[[Communications Relay Station]]s''' — 15 MRP for quick destruction
* '''[[Federate Drop Crate]]''' — 4 MRP to destroy the supplies; always worth investigating

=== Events to Skip (Save KC) ===
* Standard infantry patrols — no Accolades; pure KC drain
* Free Patrol mission — poor TRP/MRP ratio
* Valleys — optional; not needed for missions
* Fire Bases (early game) — dangerous; Sabretooth cannon can kill units
* TRAFs (before Phase 4) — too dangerous

