== General Tips ==
'''KCharge Management:'''
* KCharge is your most precious resource in Talsia — treat it as currency
* Skip all encounters that don't give TRP, Accolades, or MRP
* '''Do not fight standard infantry patrols''' — they give nothing and cost 1–2 KC each
* Only use mercs when truly necessary (generally only in Alpha Sector)
* If you die and get sent back to Workshop: do not upgrade bots too much; conserve resources and re-enter

'''BM Management:'''
* Higher BM = more XP per MRP (up to ~14M BM)
* Before Phase 4, keep BM controlled — higher BM = harder enemy squads = more KC per fight
* After Phase 4 (Pneumatron), bump BM as high as you can sustain

'''Seer Setup:'''
* Seers are the most critical element of your squad. Wrong modules on Seers lose battles. Check Personal Squad Viewer constantly to see your actual deflection, fire rate, and energy stats.
* At any given phase, your Seers' stats determine whether you can survive Alpha encounters. Prioritise Seer upgrades.

'''Mission Success Rate:'''
* Keep your success rate above 90% to work toward higher-tier awards
* Abort missions you genuinely cannot complete — a loss is worse than an abort for success rate
* At 18k TRP, you can afford to abort regularly (−50 TRP each abort) since TRP no longer matters for MRP output

'''Using [[Magma Mines]]:'''
* [[Magma Mines]] on [[Bulwark]] reduce incoming BM from attacking squads — use them on Blockade missions to lower the difficulty of reinforcement squads

'''[[Uncrewed Tanks]] and [[Comwave Scanner]]:'''
* Having a [[Comwave Scanner]] on a squad member enables hijacking Uncrewed Tanks, accessing Command Centers (Neoforina), and accessing Super Credit Caches ($500,000)
* The Comwave Scanner is a significant passive bonus — consider keeping one in your squad for these encounters

